hensive Codebase Exploration Report\\n\\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Entire CLI codebase, here's what I found:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. THE `entire enable` COMMAND IMPLEMENTATION\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/dip/Repositories/cli/cmd/entire/cli/setup.go`\\n\\n**Key Function:** `newEnableCmd()` (lines 46-161)\\n\\n**Flow Overview:**\\n1. **Prerequisites Check:** Validates that we're in a git repository (line 71)\\n2. **Initial Status Check:** Warns if the repo has no commits (line 81)\\n3. **Agent Detection/Selection:** \\n   - Automatically detects installed agents via `detectOrSelectAgent()` (lines 523-646)\\n   - If no agents detected, falls back to default agent (Claude Code)\\n4. **Setup Flow - Two Paths:**\\n   - **Non-interactive:** When `--agent` flag is provided (lines 87-100)\\n   - **Interactive:** Multi-select form for choosing agents (lines 117-126)\\n5. **Configuration:**\\n   - Loads existing settings (lines 271-276, 359-363)\\n   - Saves settings to `.entire/settings.json` or `.entire/settings.local.json` (lines 298-319, 377-401)\\n   - Installs git hooks (line 322)\\n   - Calls strategy-specific setup via `strat.EnsureSetup()` (line 330)\\n\\n**Key Helper Functions:**\\n- `detectOrSelectAgent()` - Auto-detects agents and prompts user if needed\\n- `setupAgentHooks()` - Installs agent-specific hooks\\n- `setupEntireDirectory()` - Creates `.entire/` directory and `.gitignore`\\n- `runEnableInteractive()` - Interactive flow with telemetry prompt\\n- `runEnableWithStrategy()` - Non-interactive flow with explicit strategy\\n- `setupAgentHooksNonInteractive()` - Agent hook setup for `--agent` flag\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. AGENT DETECTION & CONFIGURATION SYSTEM\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/dip/Repositories/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/`\\n\\n**Agent Registry Pattern:**\\n- **Registry Implementation:** `/Users/dip/Repositories/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go`\\n- **Factory Pattern:** Agents are registered in `init()` functions\\n- **Types:**\\n  - `AgentName` - Registry key (e.g., \\\"claude-code\\\", \\\"gemini\\\", \\\"opencode\\\")\\n  - `AgentType` - Display name for metadata (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Gemini CLI\\\")\\n\\n**Registered Agents:**\\n\\n| Agent | Registry Key | Display Name | Location | Detection |\\n|-------|--------------|--------------|----------|-----------|\\n| **Claude Code** | `claude-code` | `Claude Code` | `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/` | Checks for `.claude/` or `.claude/settings.json` |\\n| **Gemini CLI** | `gemini` | `Gemini CLI` | `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/` | Checks for `.gemini/` or `.gemini/settings.json` |\\n| **OpenCode** | `opencode` | `OpenCode` | `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/` | Checks for `.opencode/` or `opencode.json` |\\n\\n**Agent Detection Method (`agent.DetectAll()`):**\\n1. Checks all registered agents in sorted order (deterministic)\\n2. Calls `DetectPresence()` on each agent\\n3. Returns all agents where `DetectPresence()` returns true\\n\\n**Agent Registration (`registry.go`):**\\n```go\\n// Each agent registers itself in init()\\nfunc init() {\\n    agent.Register(agent.AgentNameClaudeCode, NewClaudeCodeAgent)\\n}\\n\\n// Global registry with RWMutex for thread safety\\nvar registry = make(map[AgentName]Factory)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. HOOK INSTALLATION PER AGENT\\n\\n**Location:** Agent-specific `hooks.go` files\\n\\n#### **A. Claude Code Hooks** (`agent/claudecode/hooks.go`)\\n\\n**InstallHooks() Method:**\\n- **File Modified:** `.claude/settings.json`\\n- **Hook Types Installed:**\\n  - `SessionStart`\\n  - `SessionEnd`\\n  - `Stop`\\n  - `UserPromptSubmit`\\n  - `PreToolUse` (with \\\"Task\\\" matcher)\\n  - `PostToolUse` (with \\\"Task\\\" and \\\"TodoWrite\\\" matchers)\\n- **Command Format:**\\n  - Production: `entire hooks claude-code session-start`\\n  - Development: `go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code session-start`\\n- **Permissions:** Adds deny rule `Read(./.entire/metadata/**)` to block Claude from reading