al):**\\n1. `prepare-commit-msg` - Adds context trailers\\n2. `commit-msg` - Strips trailer if no user content\\n3. `post-commit` - Condenses session data if checkpoint trailer present\\n4. `pre-push` - Pushes session logs alongside user pushes\\n\\n**Installation Process (`InstallGitHook()`):**\\n1. Creates `.git/hooks/` directory\\n2. Builds hook specifications with command prefix\\n3. For each hook:\\n   - Checks if pre-existing hook exists\\n   - If not Entire's: Backs up to `.pre-entire` suffix\\n   - Chains to backup if needed (preserves pre-existing hooks)\\n   - Writes new hook file with 0o755 permissions\\n4. Returns count of hooks installed\\n\\n**Hook Marker:** All hooks contain comment `# Entire CLI hooks` for identification\\n\\n**Backup & Restoration:**\\n- Automatic backup of pre-existing hooks to `.hook-name.pre-entire`\\n- Chain calls pre-existing hooks after Entire hook completes\\n- Graceful restoration on uninstall\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. SETTINGS SYSTEM\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/dip/Repositories/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go`\\n\\n**Settings Files:**\\n- **Primary:** `.entire/settings.json` - Project-level config\\n- **Override:** `.entire/settings.local.json` - Local machine overrides (not committed)\\n\\n**Settings Structure (`EntireSettings` struct):**\\n```go\\ntype EntireSettings struct {\\n    Strategy        string              // \\\"manual-commit\\\" or \\\"auto-commit\\\"\\n    Enabled         bool                // Enable/disable Entire\\n    LocalDev        bool                // Use \\\"go run\\\" instead of binary\\n    LogLevel        string              // \\\"debug\\\", \\\"info\\\", \\\"warn\\\", \\\"error\\\"\\n    StrategyOptions map[string]any      // Strategy-specific config (e.g., push_sessions)\\n    Telemetry       *bool               // nil (ask), true (opt-in), false (opt-out)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Settings Loading (`settings.Load()`):**\\n1. Loads base settings from `.entire/settings.json`\\n2. Merges local overrid